720883f-c.title: Manhattan: Lenox Avenue - 146th Street (West)
720883f-c.text:
lenox Avenue, west side, north from and across V. 148th
Street, showing between 146 to 147th Street the old car barn of
the New York Railway Uo. This structure, accordirg to the
Ney York Times of Mav 24, 1938, will be replaced by a new one
storv earage which is estimated to cost '250,000 and will be
occupied by the Hew York City Omnibus Corp. Note that Wompanys'
buses out side of same. Views 2 and 3 show the 146th and 147th
Streets sides respectively.
June 17, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3
P. L. Sperr
